# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok ford motor co. will make even deeper cuts to its operations in the wake of a #.# billion dollar fourth quarter loss but said thursday it had `` sufficient liquidity '' to fund its turnaround plan without us government aid .
# ::alignments
(h / have-concession-91
      :ARG1 (s / say-01
            :ARG0 (c / company
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Hartford"
                        :op2 "Motor"
                        :op3 "Co."))
            :ARG1 (h2 / have-03
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (l / liquidity
                        :ARG1-of (s2 / suffice-01)
                        :purpose (f / fund-01
                              :ARG0 c
                              :ARG1 (p / plan-01
                                    :ARG0 c
                                    :ARG1 (t / turnaround))
                              :manner (a / aid-01
                                    :polarity -
                                    :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                                          :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01))
                                    :ARG1 c))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t2 / thursday)))
      :ARG2 (c2 / cut-02
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (o / operate-01
                  :ARG0 c)
            :ARG1-of (h3 / have-degree-91
                  :ARG2 (d2 / deep-02
                        :ARG1 c2)
                  :ARG3 (m / more
                        :mod (e / even)))
            :time (w / wake
                  :op1 (l2 / lose-02
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG3 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 1000000000
                              :unit (d3 / dollar))
                        :time (q / quarter
                              :ord (o2 / ordinal-entity
                                    :value 4))))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok treasury prices rose for the fourth straight day friday , pushing yields lower , as investors pulled out of stocks and moved into safer investments .
# ::alignments
(r / rise-01
      :ARG1 (p / price-01
            :ARG1 (t / treasury))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)
            :mod (s / straight
                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 4)))
      :ARG0-of (p2 / push-01
            :ARG1 (y / yield-01)
            :ARG2 (l / lower-05
                  :ARG1 y)
            :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (a / and
                        :op1 (p3 / pull-out-02
                              :ARG1 (p4 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (ii / invest-01))
                              :ARG2 (s2 / stock))
                        :op2 (m / move-01
                              :ARG0 p4
                              :ARG2 (t2 / thing
                                    :ARG1-of ii)
                              :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                                    :ARG2 (s3 / safe-01
                                          :ARG1 t2)
                                    :ARG3 (m2 / more)))))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok iran 's police said on sunday that four people were killed and ### others arrested during clashes between anti-government protesters and security forces in tehran , iran 's satellite channel press tv reported .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (t / television
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Press"
                  :op2 "News")
            :mod (s / satellite)
            :poss (c / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Iran")))
      :ARG1 (s2 / say-01
            :ARG0 (p / police
                  :mod c)
            :ARG1 (a / and
                  :op1 (k / kill-01
                        :ARG1 (p2 / person
                              :quant 4))
                  :op2 (a2 / arrest-01
                        :ARG1 (p3 / person
                              :mod (o / other)))
                  :time (c2 / clash-01
                        :ARG0 (p4 / person
                              :ARG0-of (p5 / protest-01)
                              :ARG0-of (o2 / oppose-01
                                    :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                                          :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01))))
                        :ARG1 (f / force
                              :mod (s3 / security))
                        :location (c3 / city
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Tehran"))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (s4 / sunday))))

                                          :consist-of (t / titanium)))

                              :ARG1-of (n2 / near-02
                                    :ARG2 (r / refuge
                                          :mod (w / wildlife)
                                          :mod (n3 / nation)
                                          :location (s3 / state
                                                :name (n4 / name
                                                      :op1 "Georgia")))))))
            :op2 (d2 / discuss-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (ii / issue-02)
                  :ARG2 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (a3 / authority)
                        :op2 (g2 / group
                              :mod (e / environment)))))
      :time (d3 / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)))

# ::id 7 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                                    :op2 "flu")

                                    :degree (h2 / high-02)))
                        :ARG2 (a3 / abroad)))))

                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Germany")))))
            :ARG1 (a / allege-01
                  :ARG0 (p / person
                        :ARG0-of (c7 / consume-01))
                  :ARG1 (p2 / practice-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG1 (s / sell-01)
                        :ARG1-of (l2 / legal-02
                              :polarity -)))
            :ARG1-of (c8 / conclusive-00))
      :ARG2 c3
      :time (u / until
            :op1 (m3 / mid
                  :op1 (d2 / date-entity
                        :month 1
                        :time-of g)))
      :weekday (t / thursday))

# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Parliament"))
                  :ARG2 (o / officer
                        :topic (p2 / population)
                        :mod (c / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Kenya")))))
      :ARG1 (a / address-02
            :ARG0 (g2 / government-organization
                  :ARG0-of (g3 / govern-01
                        :ARG1 c))
            :ARG1 (h2 / health
                  :mod (r / reproduce-01)
                  :poss (w / woman))
            :ARG2 (a2 / adopt-01
                  :ARG0 g2
                  :ARG1 (p3 / paper
                        :topic (a3 / and
                              :op1 (p4 / population)
                              :op2 (d / develop-02
                                    :ARG1-of (s2 / sustain-01
                                          :ARG1-of (p5 / possible-01)))))
                  :time (r2 / recent))
            :ARG1-of (s3 / serious-01)))

      :ARG0 (d / defect-01

                        :op1 "innocuous")

                        :ARG1 (b / blueprint

                                    :ARG1 (e / enzyme
                                          :ARG1-of (k / know-02
                                                :ARG2 (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "innocuous"))))))))
      :ARG1 (d2 / disease
            :name (n3 / name
                  :op1 "Gaucher"
                  :op2 " disease")

                  :ARG1 (p2 / person
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "America"))
                        :ARG1-of (e2 / estimate-01)))))

# ::id 1902 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok figures released by the swiss federal statistics office thursday show that inflation has risen above # percent in switzerland for the first time in four years to #.# percent .
# ::alignments

            :ARG1-of (r / release-01
                  :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Swiss"
                              :op2 "Federal"
                              :op3 "Statistics"
                              :op4 "Office"))
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :weekday (t / thursday))))
      :ARG1 (r2 / rise-01
            :ARG1 (ii / inflate-01)
            :ARG2 (a / above
                  :op1 (p / percentage-entity
                        :value 1))
            :ARG4 (p2 / percentage-entity
                  :value 2)
            :location (c / country
                  :time (b / before
                        :op1 (n2 / now)
                        :duration (t2 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 4
                              :unit (y / year))))))

                        :mod (m / more)))

                        :ARG2 (l / large)
                        :ARG3 (m3 / most)
                        :ARG5 (c3 / city
                              :location (c4 / country
                                    :name (n / name
                                          :op1 "Canada"))))))
      :op2 (s2 / say-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (p2 / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (r2 / review-01
                        :ARG1 (h4 / handle-01
                              :ARG0 (t / they)

                                    :ARG1 (ii / ill-01)

                        :ARG1-of (p3 / public-02)))))
